Ex1
problem statement: Write a program to store product Manufacturers(Sony,Airtel,Jio,Nokia,Samsung) in an array
and display the data of an array with for loop.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Product Manufacturers</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Product Manufacturers</h1>

    <script>
        // Array to store product manufacturers
        var manufacturers = ["Sony", "Airtel", "Jio", "Nokia", "Samsung"];

        // Display the data using a for loop
        document.write("<ul>");
        for (var i = 0; i < manufacturers.length; i++) {
            document.write("<li>" + manufacturers[i] + "</li>");
        }
        document.write("</ul>");
    </script>
</body>
</html>
---------------------------------------
Ex2
problem statement:diplay the table of any number in the below format
2*1=2
2*2=4
2*3=6

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Multiplication Table</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Multiplication Table of 2</h1>

    <script>
        var number = 2;

        for (var i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
            var result = number * i;
            document.write(number + "*" + i + "=" + result + "<br>");
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
-----------------------------
Ex3
problem statement:
3.Write a program to display the welcome message based on gender input
e.g. if the gender input is male. then you get a message as Good afternoon Sir or if input is female then Good afternoon madam
can you string function .toLowerCase()
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Welcome Message</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome Message</h1>

    <script>
        var gender = prompt("Please enter your gender (Male/Female):").toLowerCase();

        if (gender === "male") {
            document.write("Good afternoon, Sir!");
        } else if (gender === "female") {
            document.write("Good afternoon, Madam!");
        } else {
            document.write("Gender not specified or invalid input.");
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
